<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5352.1.1>
    dc:creator "Jäger, Peter" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Revision of the huntsman spider genus Micrommata Latreille, 1804 (Sparassidae Sparassinae)" ;
    bibo:endPage "45" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-10-02" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "5352" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406890>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406917>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406919>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406921>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406925> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406890>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–3. Distribution ranges of Micrommata species. 1 M. virescens (red circles), M. diesenhoff spec. nov. (black triangle). 2 M.ligurina (red circles), M. biggi spec. nov. (black triangles).3 M. formosa (red circles), M.aljibica (black triangles). Majority of records is from specimens examined, some are from published literature or websites like iNaturalist (western record of M. aljibica, several records of M. virescens in its central range)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406890/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406917>
    dc:description "FIGURES 56–61. Micrommata formosa, left palp (56 prolateral; 57, 59 ventral; 58, 60 retrolateral; 61 tegulum tip and embolic division, ventral) (56–58 from Israel; 59–61 male from Spain)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406917/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406919>
    dc:description "FIGURES 62–67. Micrommata formosa, female copulatory organ (62, 66 epigyne, ventral; 63 ditto, posterior; 64, 67 vulva, dorsal; 65 schematic course of IDS, dorsal) (62–65 holotype female of M. aragonensis from Spain; 66–67 female from Spain); photo credits: 66–67 Arnaud Henrard. EP—epigynal pocket." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406919/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406921>
    dc:description "FIGURES 68–72. Micrommata formosa, female copulatory organ (68, 71 epigyne, ventral; 69, 72 ditto, posterior; 70 vulva, dorsal (68–70 from Israel; 71–72 from Tunisia)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406921/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406925>
    dc:description "FIGURES 73–83. Micrommata formosa, habitus of preserved (73–79) and live (80–83) spiders (73, 75, 78, 80, 82–83 dorsal; 74, 76, 79 ventral; 77 lateral; 81 frontal) (73–74 male from Spain; 75–77 holotype female of M. aragonensis from Spain; 78–81 female from Spain; 82 female from Malta; 83 female with opened egg sac from Portugal). Photo credits: 78–81 Arnaud Henrard; 82 Victor Falzon; 83 Sergio Henriques." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406925/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

